# 1391. Check if There is a Valid Path in a Grid

**Difficulty:** Medium  
**Topic:** BFS, Graph, Matrix  
**Date:** April 2026

## Problem Summary
Grid mein streets hain (1-6 types), check karo ki (0,0) se 
(m-1,n-1) tak valid path hai ya nahi.

## Approach
BFS use kiya. Key insight — **bidirectional check**:
- Current cell ka exit hona chahiye
- Neighbor cell ka opposite entry hona chahiye

## Bugs I faced (most important part! 🔑)

### Bug 1 — Boundary condition
```cpp
// ❌ Wrong
if(Dr<0 || Dr>m ...)   // > instead of >=

// ✅ Fixed  
if(Dr<0 || Dr>=m ...)
```

### Bug 2 — Wrong cell reference
```cpp
// ❌ Wrong — dono mein neighbor check kar raha tha
bool Curr_exist = street[grid[Dr][Dc]].count(exit_dr);

// ✅ Fixed — current cell alag, neighbor alag
bool Curr_exist  = street[grid[r][c]].count(exit_dr);
bool Neigh_entry = street[grid[Dr][Dc]].count(enter_dc);
```

## What I learned
- Off-by-one errors bohot common hain boundary checks mein
- Variable names carefully choose karo (Dr,Dc vs r,c)
- Jab wrong answer aaye — pehle variable references check karo

## Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool hasValidPath(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        queue<pair<int,int>>q;
        int m=grid.size();
        int n=grid[0].size();
        if(m==1 && n==1){
            return true;
        }
      vector<tuple<int,int,int,int>>directions={
        {0,-1,0,1},
       {0,1,1,0},
       {-1,0,2,3},
       {1,0,3,2}
      };
      unordered_map<int,unordered_set<int>>street={
       {1, {0,1}},{2,{2,3}},{3,{0,3}},{4,{1,3}},{5,{0,2}},{6,{1,2}}
      };
      vector<vector<bool>>visited(m,vector<bool>(n,false));
        q.push({0,0});
        visited[0][0]=true;
        while(!q.empty()){
            auto[r,c]=q.front();
            q.pop();
        for(auto &[dr,dc,exit_dr,enter_dc]:directions){
           int Dr=r+dr;
           int Dc=c+dc;
           if(Dr<0|| Dr>=m || Dc<0 ||Dc>=n) continue;
           if(visited[Dr][Dc]) continue;

           bool Curr_exist=street[grid[r][c]].count(exit_dr);
           bool Neigh_entry=street[grid[Dr][Dc]].count(enter_dc);
           if(Curr_exist && Neigh_entry){
            if(Dr ==m-1 && Dc== n-1) return true;
            visited[Dr][Dc]=true;
            q.push({Dr,Dc});
           }
        }
        }
        return false;
    }
};
